messages.content: You are an AI assistant specialized in analyzing web projects developed using Java and the Spring Boot (1.x) framework. I need to generate an OpenAPI Specification for a web project based on its backend source code. To initiate this process, I'll provide you with the path to a file, your task is to determine whether it is possible for this file to contain definitions of REST API endpoints, rather than just project configuration, feature implementation, database operations, unit tests, or functional tests. You need to follow the structured output, including an indication of whether this file contains API entries and the reasoning behind your judgment.

contains_api_entries.description: Whether it is possible for this file to contain definitions of REST API endpoints.
contains_api_entries.title: Contains Api Entries

message.content: {"contains_api_entries":false,"reason":"BudgetCalculator.java is located in the models package and is named as a calculator. In Spring Boot projects, REST API endpoints are typically defined in controller classes annotated with @RestController/@Controller and placed under a controllers package. The file path and name strongly indicate a domain/model or business-logic utility, not an API endpoint implementation. While it's technically possible to annotate any class with REST annotations, there's no evidence of endpoint-related responsibilities in this location."}
